@realmoney Ss Over Ns Into Year End? I would say the consensus view is that should the market rally into the year end, that advance would likely led by higher beta technology names. I am taking the contrarian view - suggesting many of the non Nasdaq related stocks
(that have sold off dramatically) will lead the year end rally. Remember Mr. Market often does what hurts the most people! And that is how I am playing it! @jimcramer @tomkeene @saraeisen

I like the action off of the possible capitulation lows of a few days ago. I like the turn towards negative sentiment, some positive divergences, the fear, the oversolds, etc. Anticipatory investing/trading vs Reactionary - the fundamental difference in our approaches.

I see discounts in a number of stocks relative to intrinsic value. You want to see confirmation in price. Both reasonable approaches. I do think, however if I am right on the year end rally - I will be selling when you are buying! A respectful observation, not being a wise guy.
